PART 3: PARAMETRIC RESONANCE — MATHIEU EQUATION
======================================================================

Q_k as Fejér kernel samples:
  Q_k = m² · F_m(2πk/p) where F_m(t) = (1/m)(sin(mt/2)/sin(t/2))²

  p= 7, m=3: Q_k/m² = [0.560991 0.03422  0.071456]
  p=11, m=5: Q_k/m² = [0.493742 0.010862 0.057948 0.01413  0.023319]
  p=13, m=6: Q_k/m² = [0.477968 0.007366 0.055227 0.008857 0.02152  0.012395]
  p=17, m=8: Q_k/m² = [0.458833 0.004043 0.052159 0.004493 0.019661 0.005404 0.010756 0.007153]

KEY: Q_k = m² · F_m(2πk/p) means the Q-spectrum is a SAMPLED Fejér kernel.
The Fejér kernel is ALWAYS non-negative and has a single peak at t=0.
This is the spectral signature of the Interval's consecutive structure.

